# Strategy #strategy
style: section

2026-05-01: Research cake styles and choose a recipe #strategy
Classic vanilla layer cake with Swiss meringue buttercream. Serves 12.

## Goal — Gather ingredients #strategy
2026-05-02: Create detailed shopping list #strategy
Flour, sugar, eggs, butter, baking powder, vanilla extract, milk, salt. Cross-reference against pantry.

2026-05-03: Procure all ingredients from store #strategy
Check expiration dates. Bring everything to room temperature.

# Tooling #tooling
style: section

2026-05-04: Verify all baking equipment is available #tooling
Stand mixer, measuring cups and spoons, rubber spatulas, 9-inch round cake pans, cooling racks, offset spatula.

## Goal — Prepare the workspace #tooling
2026-05-05: Preheat oven to 350°F #tooling
Position rack in the center. Line cake pans with parchment rounds.

2026-05-05: Grease and flour cake pans #tooling
Apply butter evenly, dust with flour, tap out excess.

# Workbench #workbench
style: section

## Goal — Mix dry ingredients #workbench
2026-05-06: Sift flour, baking powder, and salt together #workbench
Whisk in a medium bowl until evenly combined. Set aside.

## Goal — Cream butter and sugar #workbench
2026-05-07: Beat butter on medium speed until smooth #workbench
Gradually add sugar, beat for 3-4 minutes until light and fluffy.

2026-05-08: Add eggs one at a time, then vanilla #workbench
Beat well after each addition. Scrape down the bowl.

## Goal — Combine wet and dry #workbench
2026-05-09: Alternately add dry ingredients and milk #workbench
Start and end with dry. Mix until just combined — do not overmix.

# Product #product
style: section

2026-05-10: FIRST MILESTONE — Batter is ready, pans are prepared #product #milestone

2026-05-10 9:00am: Divide batter evenly between prepared pans #product
Use a kitchen scale for accuracy — 450g per pan.

2026-05-10 9:15am - 2026-05-10 10:00am: Bake at 350°F #product
Rotate pans halfway through. Test with a toothpick at 35 minutes.

2026-05-10 10:00am: Cool cakes in pans for 10 minutes #product
Then turn out onto wire racks. Cool completely before frosting.

# Growth #growth
style: section

## Goal — Make the buttercream #growth
2026-05-11: Whip butter until light and fluffy #growth
Use room temperature butter. Beat on medium-high for 5 minutes.

2026-05-12: Gradually add sifted powdered sugar #growth
Add in batches. Scrape bowl frequently.

2026-05-13: Add vanilla and cream until desired consistency #growth
Beat on low until incorporated, then high for 30 seconds.

## Goal — Color and portion #growth
2026-05-14: Divide frosting into portions for tinting #growth
Reserve 1 cup for crumb coat. Tint remaining in pastel gradient.

# Finance #finance
style: section

2026-05-15: Calculate total ingredient cost #finance
Flour $2.49, sugar $3.99, eggs $4.29, butter $5.49, vanilla $6.99, milk $2.89, powdered sugar $4.99.

2026-05-16: Overhead and utility cost estimate #finance
Oven electricity $0.45, mixer electricity $0.08, parchment paper $0.15.

2026-05-17: Cost per slice analysis #finance
Total $31.82 ÷ 12 slices = $2.65 per slice. Comparable bakery slice: $6.50.

# Personal #personal
style: section

2026-05-18: SECOND MILESTONE — Cake cooled, frosting ready #personal #milestone

## Goal — Assemble the cake #personal
2026-05-18: Level cake layers with a serrated knife #personal
Remove domed tops to create flat, even layers.

2026-05-19: Apply crumb coat and chill #personal
Thin layer of frosting seals in crumbs. Refrigerate for 30 minutes.

## Goal — Final decoration #personal
2026-05-20: Apply final layer of frosting #personal
Smooth with a bench scraper. Clean edges on top.

2026-05-21: Pipe decorative border and add toppings #personal
Fresh berries, edible flowers, and a drizzle of caramel.

2026-05-22: THIRD MILESTONE — Cake complete! Slice and serve #personal #milestone
Enjoy with coffee or tea. Share with friends and family.

